There are minor blooms about 10 miles (16 km) off the coast in Hillsborough County, but there are fewer than last week.
There have also been reports of flooding in Pasco County.
Medium concentrations in or at sea have been reported in Pinellas County during the last week, low to high concentrations in the sea off Hillsborough County, background concentration to high concentrations in Manatee County, background concentration to high concentrations in or in the sea off Sarasota County, background concentration to medium concentrations in Charlotte County, background concentration to high concentrations in or in the sea off Lee County and low concentrations in Collier.
Breathing difficulties continue to be reported in Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Lee and Collier.
There have been no reports of respiratory problems in northwest Florida in the past week.
